# MODULAR: Netlify redirect rules. The first set covers
# SPA-style fallback; the favicon block makes sure the
# crawler doesn't 404 even if the .ico is missing from
# the deploy.

# SPA fallback: any unknown path under / falls through to
# index.html so the static deploy behaves like the proxy.
/*    /index.html   200

# MODULAR: emoji favicon. /favicon.ico is the legacy default
# that browsers + crawlers still ask for; redirect to the
# SVG (which the link tag in index.html declares as primary).
# If the .ico file is present in the deploy, the redirect is
# a no-op; if it's missing, the redirect is the safety net.
/favicon.ico  /favicon.svg  301
